Five pedestrians were killed in Pietermaritzburg and Newcastle on Saturday. Emergency Medical Services spokesperson, Robert Mckenzie, said that paramedics first attended to a pedestrian killed in Osizweni, Newcastle. While they were on their way back to the base, they came across another scene, where people were gathered around a cow which had been knocked by a car. He said that while the people were busy clearing the scene, a passing vehicle knocked two of the community members who died at the scene. Meanwhile, on Saturday morning, two pedestrians were knocked in the Pietermaritzburg CBD by two vehicles which crashed into each other. Road Traffic Inspectorate spokesperson, Zinhle Mngomezulu, said the collision occurred at the corners of Boshoff and Jabu Ndlovu streets . The drivers and passengers of both vehicles, a Toyota Etios and Mercedes, were not seriously injured.